                            <h1>Wandpoint</h1>
                            <p>
                                Wandpoint is a handheld AR projection device used in the old streets that releases and interprets architectural memories which disappear over time. During the day, the old block continues to exist as a commercial and cultural area; at night, wandpoint brings people back in time and allows them to enjoy the past life scenes by creating a nostalgic atmosphere
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                Wandpoint, as a storyteller, introduces users into an interesting narrative space. Users need to take the initiative to explore, and the illuminated houses, vegetation and interior furnishings will show what they were like years ago.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                Wandpoint enhances tourism and root-seeking value in the area. For tourists, it recreates the original appearance of the area in an immersive way, thereby playing a role in science and entertainment. For locals, it satisfies nostalgia and enhances the sense of belonging.
